---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About">
  <article class="prose-measure mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">About this site</h1>

    <p>NoChrome is a NY-specific resource hub for parents researching their options around school-issued K-5 device programs. It is built and maintained by parents in New York State. It is not affiliated with any school district, advocacy organization, or political campaign.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Why this exists</h2>
    <p>Most NY districts have a 1:1 device program. Most parents do not know what data their child's school is sharing with which vendors, whether their district has posted the Parents Bill of Rights for Data Privacy that NY Education Law §2-d requires, or what their options are if they're uncomfortable with the program. This site collects what is publicly available, flags what is not, and points parents to the procedures (FOIL, board meetings, opt-out letters) that exist to fill in the gaps.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">How to suggest a correction</h2>
    <p>If you find a district detail that is wrong or out of date, the most useful thing you can send is a link to the source document. Email corrections to the address in the repository, or open an issue on the project's GitHub.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">How to contribute a district</h2>
    <p>The site's seed data covers Columbia, Dutchess, and Greene counties. Contributions covering other NY counties are welcome. The contribution standard is in the README. Briefly: every district fact needs a public source link and a verification date.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">What we don't do</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
      <li>We don't track visitors. No analytics, no cookies, no accounts.</li>
      <li>We don't accept donations or run a newsletter.</li>
      <li>We don't give legal advice. Consult an education attorney for your specific situation.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</Layout>
